				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6138242/scp-3632#post-3836996</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 15 Jun 2018 20:55:08 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Decibelles</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2005044</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I enjoyed it, and it continues to ramp up the absurdity while not suspending my disbelief too much. The final note killed it for me, however. Exposition of things we already know while not adding much to the mix at the very end of an article is a tired way of writing skips, so no-vote. The Recovery &amp; Analysis may go on for a little too long, but I liked it, and it's a minor complaint compared to the note.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6138242#post-3836014</guid>
				<title>Thoth is smart bird</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6138242/scp-3632#post-3836014</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 14 Jun 2018 22:30:05 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>InsanePigeon</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3495497</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>One of my favorite things about the Team Bird entries is Thoth. Unlike a lot of other &quot;godly&quot; being on the wiki, Thoth isn't simply a force of nature or singular in his goals. He is a crafty, calculating being that is a fresh of breath air from the typical godlike skips I see here and there.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
